    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-04T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="734"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/933</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-04T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1197. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>
                    [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 90. Your 81, Embassy’s 1366, May 28, 10 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d734fn1">Not
                        printed.</note>
                    <persName>Smith</persName> will arrive Madrid about June 20 to take up shipping
                    negotiation. He advises and you may announce, if you approve, an extension of
                    our arrangement of March 7<note n="2" xml:id="d734fn2">See note of Mar. 7 from
                        the Ambassador in Spain to the Spanish Minister of State, <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1671">p. 1671</ref>.</note> respecting
                    bunker regulations to and including June 25. <persName>Cailler</persName>
                    representing Swiss Government is proceeding to Madrid to negotiate for enemy
                    boats in Spain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
